  "excerpt": "<p>Export DataTools Pro metrics glossary to Notion with our direct API integration.</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-wideright\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"ff8a65\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #ff8a65;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/icons8-coda-240.png\" alt=\"Coda\" class=\"wp-image-9926 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/icons8-coda-240.png 240w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/icons8-coda-240-150x150.png 150w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/icons8-coda-240-45x45.png 45w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 240px) 100vw, 240px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>Import your DataTools Pro metrics glossary into Coda with our Coda Bundle. This secured integration allows you to seamlessly pull metrics definitions into Coda and distribute directly business users. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn more about <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/lesson/metrics-glossary-for-salesforce/\" title=\"Building Metrics Glossary for Salesforce with DataTools Pro\">DataTools Pro Metrics Glossary</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn about other <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/integrations/\" title=\"DataTools Pro Integrations for Metrics Governance\">DataTools Pro integrations</a></p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-1 one-column\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Metrics Governance with Salesforce, Coda and DataTools Pro\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/axKBfGYNdio?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Generate a DataTools Pro API Key for Coda</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 1: <a href=\"https://app.datatoolspro.com/user/coda\" title=\"DataTools Pro Notion Settings\">Access Coda settings page</a> or click on the Coda icon on the Metrics Glossary page</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f3f7f6\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"888\" height=\"371\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-10.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9976 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f3f7f6; width:367px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-10.png 888w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-10-300x125.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-10-768x321.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 2: Click &#8220;Create API Key&#8221; button</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 3: Save your API key to a secured location. DataTools Pro will display your API key only one time, and by design will not query and display the key.</p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Install the Bundle</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Visit the DataTools Pro Coda page to access your Coda Bundle.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Using the DataTools Pro Coda Bundle</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>On any Coda page start typing the following short code to display your installed pack.</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>/datatools</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9f9f9\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"681\" height=\"393\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-19.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9990 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9f9f9; width:326px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-19.png 681w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-19-300x173.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 681px) 100vw, 681px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 2. Click on DataTools Pro Metric Glossary</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 3. On the right side bar, you will see Building Blocks including &#8220;DataTools Pro Sync&#8221;.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 4. Drag DataTools Pro sync onto your Coda canvas</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f6f6f6\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"627\" height=\"639\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-21.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9992 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f6f6f6; width:410px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-21.png 627w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-21-294x300.png 294w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-21-45x45.png 45w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 627px) 100vw, 627px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 5. Click the &#8220;Sync Now&#8221; button within the table or within the Table Options</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f1f2f3\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f1f2f3;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"503\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-20-1024x503.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9991 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-20-1024x503.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-20-300x147.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-20-768x377.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-20-1536x755.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-20-2048x1006.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 6. Paste your DataTools Pro API Key for Coda to authorize Coda to connect.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 7. Select a line of business or topic to restrict the metrics loaded</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f7f7f7\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"594\" height=\"553\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-22.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9993 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f7f7f7; width:305px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-22.png 594w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-22-300x279.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 8. Set a refresh interval to automatically sync and update your metrics glossary to ensure it is always up to date.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"e3eaf1\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"603\" height=\"459\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-24.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9995 has-transparency\" style=\"--dominant-color: #e3eaf1; width:324px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-24.png 603w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-24-300x228.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 603px) 100vw, 603px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Step 9. Use native Coda table functions to further filter, sort, group and organize your metrics glossary to your business needs</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f6f7f8\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f6f7f8;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"523\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-23-1024x523.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9994 has-transparency\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-23-1024x523.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-23-300x153.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-23-768x392.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-23-1536x784.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-23.png 1678w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n"
}